From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000008 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Jun 2026 16:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mfd: omap-usb-host: steelhead UHH_HOSTCONFIG to match vendor

On the Nexus Q the soldered SMSC LAN9500A enumerates fine under the vendor 3.0
kernel but not mainline, even though GPIOs/clock/reset/VBUS and the USB3320 ULPI
PHY state are identical (verified live: OTG_CTRL=0x66 both, PORTSC CCS=1 vendor /
CCS=0 mainline). The one register that differs is UHH_HOSTCONFIG: vendor=0x11C
(P1_CONNECT_STATUS set, APP_START_CLK clear), mainline sets APP_START_CLK and
leaves P1_CONNECT_STATUS at the reset default. Match the vendor so EHCI latches
the port-1 connect. Also log the before/after value (info) for verification.

TEST patch (diagnostic dev_info included); fold/clean up once confirmed.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
---
--- a/drivers/mfd/omap-usb-host.c
+++ b/drivers/mfd/omap-usb-host.c
@@ -441,11 +441,21 @@
 	pm_runtime_get_sync(dev);
 
 	reg = usbhs_read(omap->uhh_base, OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG);
+	dev_info(dev, "steelhead: UHH_HOSTCONFIG before = %#x\n", reg);
 	/* setup ULPI bypass and burst configurations */
 	reg |= (OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_INCR4_BURST_EN
 			| OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_INCR8_BURST_EN
 			| OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_INCR16_BURST_EN);
-	reg |= OMAP4_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_APP_START_CLK;
+	/*
+	 * Steelhead: match the vendor's working UHH_HOSTCONFIG (= 0x11C). The
+	 * soldered SMSC LAN9500A only reports connect on EHCI when
+	 * P1_CONNECT_STATUS (bit 8) is set, and the vendor leaves APP_START_CLK
+	 * (bit 31) CLEAR so the UHH does not auto clock-gate and drop the port.
+	 * Mainline does the opposite (APP_START_CLK set, P1_CONNECT_STATUS at the
+	 * reset default), so the EHCI never latches the connect (PORTSC CCS=0).
+	 */
+	reg |= OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_P1_CONNECT_STATUS;
+	reg &= ~OMAP4_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_APP_START_CLK;
 	reg &= ~OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_INCRX_ALIGN_EN;
 
 	switch (omap->usbhs_rev) {
@@ -463,7 +473,7 @@
 	}
 
 	usbhs_write(omap->uhh_base, OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG, reg);
-	dev_dbg(dev, "UHH setup done, uhh_hostconfig=%x\n", reg);
+	dev_info(dev, "steelhead: UHH setup done, uhh_hostconfig=%#x (vendor=0x11c)\n", reg);
 
 	pm_runtime_put_sync(dev);
 }
